description:
&lt;p&gt;We are on an ambitious plan to be the leader and innovator of community and specialist CAMHS services and to do this we are seeking a positive leader with experience of mental health to lead us on our journey to excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will lead on a dedicated portfolio of services to deliver agreed strategic objectives whilst contributing to the clinical service improvement strategies which are compatible with national and local commissioning intentions and the delivery of modern health care for children, young people and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will report directly to the Associate Director Mental Health and support them in the delivery of services and effective business management. The ability to succeed in a complex environment is a must and you will be required to deputise on behalf of the Divisional Associate Director.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time in the Division and we seek candidates with drive and passion to join us who can deliver outstanding services to our young people and their families. Should you wish to learn more about this role please contact David Pullen-Higham.&lt;/p&gt;
